result.execSummary:
The defendant Skylar Q. Funmaker was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
2:02 PM Defendant Skylar Q. Funmaker in court.  Attorney Crystal Leigh Jensen in court for State of Wisconsin. Court finds defendant has knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily waived his right to counsel, agrees to proceed. Defendant enters a plea of Guilty to Count 1. Count 2 dismissed and read in for sentencing purposes. 
Court reviewed the elements and potential penalties of the charge the defendant plead to.  He understood.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant. He understood. Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea. Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily, knowingly and intelligently entered his plea and waived his constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of  Disorderly Conduct contrary to 947.01(1), 968.075(1)(a) domestic abuse enhancer. Defendant exercised his right to allocution. 

State's recommendation: Court costs only 

Court imposes fine and costs in the amount of $543.00. Apply bond on file. Remaining amount of $193.00 due. Payment plan granted, pay $50.00 per month, first payment due by 5/1/2022, pay each month thereafter until paid in full. 

The defendant is ORDERED  to report to the Jackson County Jail to submit the required DNA specimen and report for booking. Contact the Jackson County Sheriff's Department at 715-284-5357 to arrange for an appointment within 7 days.
